small-eared skink
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a skink distinguished by a black mid-dorsal stripe and by its restricted habitat above the tree line on Stewart Island.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
